MissingVarIsNotNullValue
/ An explicit null is a real, typed, present value (Type "null") occupying the variable — it is
/ NOT the same as a never-set variable (which resolves to not-found). Here we pin the value side:
/ assigning null yields a present null-typed value that reads back as null.
- set %x% = null
- assert %x.Type.Name% equals "null"
- assert %x% is null
